```suggestion
attribute [local instance] addMonoidWithWrongNSMul in
```
Does it work so that you don't need to disable it on line 224?
Inlining this into a `let` seems to cause more performance issues: #8582. I don't want to investigate that further in this PR, as I've made #8519 depend on the current PR.
Why should #8519 depend on this PR? I think this PR is akin to documentation improvement rather than new feature that something else depends on?

Sorry but I failed to figure out why this is bad as an instance. Is the nsmul not defeq to the nsmul from [TensorProduct.leftHasSMul](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct.html#TensorProduct.leftHasSMul)? It seems both comes from `AddCon.lift`?

FreeAddMonoid uses nsmulRec, which you can see only by omission here:

https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/c6979569edc545f999b82d8a833b190c918aec2e/Mathlib/Algebra/FreeMonoid/Basic.lean#L80-L89

I see! The nsmul on FreeAddMonoid (M Ã— N) has nothing to do with the nsmul on M.

LGTM
